The paper deals with the problem of uplink pilot contamination in Massive MIMO systems, which is a well-known issue in the field of Information Theory (cs.IT). The proposed solution involves the use of machine learning techniques to predict Channel State Information (CSI), which falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also introduces an online learning algorithm, which is a common topic in Machine Learning (cs.LG). The use of machine learning for CSI prediction can also be considered as an application of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the proposed method involves the creation and update of a CSI map, which can be seen as a control system, falling under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
